    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="245"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20437/85.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have had conference with the secretary of state for foreign affairs, who assures
                    me that the American potash contracts will in no respect be invalidate or
                    impaired by the new law, which as finally modified puts it in the hands of the
                    Bundesrat to fix prices so that the existing contracts will not be affected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
